cat2600TsFwVer.name: cat2600TsFwVer
cat2600TsFwVer.description: The firmware version in the form major.minor. For port microcode (SOLO) version information see the mgmt.mib-2.interfaces.ifTable.ifEntry.ifDescr object.

cat2600TsHwVer.name: cat2600TsHwVer
cat2600TsHwVer.description: The hardware version in the form major.minor.

cat2600TsInstallationDate.name: cat2600TsInstallationDate
cat2600TsInstallationDate.description: Firmware installation date. This date is initially set by the Network Management station. Each time the NV RAM is cleared through the console this date needs to be set by the management station. This should be in the format YYYY MM DD HH MM SS.

cat2600TsFwSize.name: cat2600TsFwSize
cat2600TsFwSize.description: Size in bytes of the binary firmware image.

cat2600TsIpAddr.name: cat2600TsIpAddr
cat2600TsIpAddr.description: IP address of the switch. Changes to this object take effect immediately.

cat2600TsNetMask.name: cat2600TsNetMask
cat2600TsNetMask.description: IP subnet mask of the switch. Changes to this object take effect immediately.

cat2600TsDefaultGateway.name: cat2600TsDefaultGateway
cat2600TsDefaultGateway.description: IP default gateway used by the switch. Changes to this object take effect immediately.

cat2600TsTrapRcvrTable.name: cat2600TsTrapRcvrTable
cat2600TsTrapRcvrTable.description: A table of managers to which to send traps. Entries in the table are saved across resets and power cycles.

cat2600TsTrapRcvrEntry.name: cat2600TsTrapRcvrEntry
cat2600TsTrapRcvrEntry.description: Definition of rows in the trap receiver table. The column cat2600TsTrapRcvrStatus is used to create and delete rows in the table. Creation requires a SET PDU with objects cat2600TsTrapRcvrStatus, cat2600TsTrapRcvrIpAddress, and cat2600TsTrapRcvrComm.

cat2600TsTrapRcvrIndex.name: cat2600TsTrapRcvrIndex
cat2600TsTrapRcvrIndex.description: The index of the row in the table.

cat2600TsTrapRcvrStatus.name: cat2600TsTrapRcvrStatus
cat2600TsTrapRcvrStatus.description: Setting the value of this object to invalid(3) deletes the row from the table. The value invalid(3) should never be returned on a GET. Setting this value to create(4) causes a new row to be created if the row does not already exist. To create a new row set cat2600TsTrapRcvrStatus to create(4) and cat2600TsTrapRcvrIndex to the next available index ( cat2600TsTrapRcvrNext ). After successful creation of the new row, you can then set the desired values for cat2600TsTrapRcvrIpAddress and cat2600TsTrapRcvrComm. The value returned on GETs should be valid(2) or other(1), which is used to indicate any other condition.

cat2600TsTrapRcvrIpAddress.name: cat2600TsTrapRcvrIpAddress
cat2600TsTrapRcvrIpAddress.description: IP address for an SNMP manager that is to receive the trap.

cat2600TsTrapRcvrDmns.name: cat2600TsTrapRcvrDmns
cat2600TsTrapRcvrDmns.description: Domains on which traps to this target are sent. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight domains, with the first octet specifying domains 0 through 7, the second octet specifying domains 8 through 15, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered domain, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered domain. Thus, each domain is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that domain is included in the set of ports which will receive the trap; the domain is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

cat2600TsPingInterval.name: cat2600TsPingInterval
cat2600TsPingInterval.description: This variable specifies the interval in seconds of sending ICMP Echo Requests to the default gateway. No PING packets will be sent if the value is set to 0. The default interval is 10 minutes.

cat2600TsTapPort.name: cat2600TsTapPort
cat2600TsTapPort.description: Select the port to monitor traffic.

cat2600TsTapMonitoredPort.name: cat2600TsTapMonitoredPort
cat2600TsTapMonitoredPort.description: Allows the selection of the port that will be monitored by the port selected by cat2600TsTapPort.

cat2600TsCrcThresholdHi.name: cat2600TsCrcThresholdHi
cat2600TsCrcThresholdHi.description: Threshold for the switch to change to store and forward mode. A change in mode also generates a trap.

cat2600TsCrcThresholdLow.name: cat2600TsCrcThresholdLow
cat2600TsCrcThresholdLow.description: Threshold for the switch to change to store and forward mode. A change in mode also generates a trap.

cat2600TsPortSwitchModeChangeTrapEnable.name: cat2600TsPortSwitchModeChangeTrapEnable
cat2600TsPortSwitchModeChangeTrapEnable.description: Enable or disable the trap sent out when the switching mode changes from cut-through to store and forward.

cat2600TsTrendThreshold.name: cat2600TsTrendThreshold
cat2600TsTrendThreshold.description: Based on trend calculation of the Dynamic Cut State algorithm, when this value is exceeded the port changes from cut-through to store and forward mode. The default value for this object is 8 events. The valid range is 1-100.

cat2600TsSamplingPeriod.name: cat2600TsSamplingPeriod
cat2600TsSamplingPeriod.description: Sampling period in minutes for determining if the error rate of CRC errors has been exceeded. The default value for this object is 10 minutes. The valid range is 1-120.

cat2600TsNumberUFC.name: cat2600TsNumberUFC
cat2600TsNumberUFC.description: The number of UFCs installed in the switch. A value of zero (or an SNMP error of NOSUCH) indicates there are NO UFCs installed in this switch. This value indicates the number of entries in the cat2600TsUFCTable.

cat2600TsNumPorts.name: cat2600TsNumPorts
cat2600TsNumPorts.description: The maximum number of physical ports on the switch. This value includes all base ports plus all ports on any UFC cards. It does not include internally defined Bridge Relay Function ports or the CPU 'interface'.

cat2600TsNumStations.name: cat2600TsNumStations
cat2600TsNumStations.description: Aggregate number of currently active stations (nodes) on all ports on the switch.

cat2600TsMostStations.name: cat2600TsMostStations
cat2600TsMostStations.description: Highest aggregate number of stations ever active on all ports at one time, since the last reset or power cycle. This includes the default MAC address entries from each port.

cat2600TsMaxStations.name: cat2600TsMaxStations
cat2600TsMaxStations.description: Highest aggregate number of stations which the switch can support simultaneously.

cat2600TsReset.name: cat2600TsReset
cat2600TsReset.description: This object is used to reset the switch. Writing softReset(3) causes the switch to reset the hardware, run quick diagnostics, clear all counters, start switching, issue a warmstart trap, and then be able to respond to SNMP requests. Writing hardReset(2) causes the switch to run power up diagnostics and then execute a soft reset. Note: all address tables are cleared in both cases. The administrative parameters from nonvolatile memory are used to initialize the operational parameters. The value returned on GETs should be running(1).

cat2600TsNumResets.name: cat2600TsNumResets
cat2600TsNumResets.description: Number of soft resets the switch has executed since the last hard reset or power cycle. Soft resets are defined as writing softReset(3) to cat2600TsReset, pressing the front panel reset button, executing a soft reset from the console, or resets induced by the switch firmware.

cat2600TsAddrAgingTime.name: cat2600TsAddrAgingTime
cat2600TsAddrAgingTime.description: Number of minutes of inactivity before an address entity is aged out. A value of zero means no aging. Note: if an address shows up on another port, the original port to address assignment is automatically deleted. The value is saved across resets and power cycles. The default value for this object is 5 minutes.

cat2600TsSysTemperature.name: cat2600TsSysTemperature
cat2600TsSysTemperature.description: Temperature condition of the system. A change in this value generates a TRAP.

cat2600TsInstalledMemory.name: cat2600TsInstalledMemory
cat2600TsInstalledMemory.description: Total amount of CPU memory installed (in megabytes).

cat2600TsSysCurTime.name: cat2600TsSysCurTime
cat2600TsSysCurTime.description: Current time at the switch. To set the time use the format yyyy mm dd hh mm ss. All fields are required.

cat2600TsPortTable.name: cat2600TsPortTable
cat2600TsPortTable.description: A table of information about each port. The number of rows is given by cat2600TsNumPorts. (This value refers to PHYSICAL ports as opposed to internal logical CRF bridge ports.)

cat2600TsPortEntry.name: cat2600TsPortEntry
cat2600TsPortEntry.description: Definition of rows in the port table. The number of rows is determined by the hardware and is specified by the value of cat2600TsNumPorts. Rows can not be created or deleted via SNMP requests.

cat2600TsPortIndex.name: cat2600TsPortIndex
cat2600TsPortIndex.description: The ifIndex value corresponding to each port entry. For TR interfaces, the TsPortIndex corresponds to the Port Number or POE Index.

cat2600TsPortRcvLocalFrames.name: cat2600TsPortRcvLocalFrames
cat2600TsPortRcvLocalFrames.description: Number of frames received where the destination is on this port.

cat2600TsPortForwardedFrames.name: cat2600TsPortForwardedFrames
cat2600TsPortForwardedFrames.description: Number of frames received on this port and forwarded to another port or the system module for processing.

cat2600TsPortMostStations.name: cat2600TsPortMostStations
cat2600TsPortMostStations.description: Highest number of stations ever active at any time since the last reset of the switch as seen by this port. This includes the default MAC address entries for the port.

cat2600TsPortMaxStations.name: cat2600TsPortMaxStations
cat2600TsPortMaxStations.description: Maximum number of stations which the port can support simultaneously.

cat2600TsPortSWHandledFrames.name: cat2600TsPortSWHandledFrames
cat2600TsPortSWHandledFrames.description: Number of Frames received on this port and delivered to the system module for processing.

cat2600TsPortLocalStations.name: cat2600TsPortLocalStations
cat2600TsPortLocalStations.description: Number of stations on this port's address table which belong to the segment attached to this port.

cat2600TsPortRemoteStations.name: cat2600TsPortRemoteStations
cat2600TsPortRemoteStations.description: Number of stations on this port's address table which belong to segments attached to other ports.

cat2600TsPortUnknownStaFrames.name: cat2600TsPortUnknownStaFrames
cat2600TsPortUnknownStaFrames.description: Number of unicast frames received on this port and forwarded to the system module for processing because the source or destination station address is not in the port's forwarding table.

cat2600TsPortResetStats.name: cat2600TsPortResetStats
cat2600TsPortResetStats.description: Setting this object to reset(3) causes all traffic counters for this port to be set to zero. Also the value of cat2600TsPortResetTimer is set to zero.

cat2600TsPortResetTimer.name: cat2600TsPortResetTimer
cat2600TsPortResetTimer.description: Time (in 100th second ticks) since the port counters were reset.

cat2600TsPortResetAddrs.name: cat2600TsPortResetAddrs
cat2600TsPortResetAddrs.description: Setting this object to reset(3) clears all address table entries for this port as well as setting all port traffic counters to zero and setting cat2600TsPortResetTimer to zero.

cat2600TsPortRcvBcasts.name: cat2600TsPortRcvBcasts
cat2600TsPortRcvBcasts.description: Number of Broadcast Frames received on this port without errors.

cat2600TsPortSwitchedFrames.name: cat2600TsPortSwitchedFrames
cat2600TsPortSwitchedFrames.description: Number of frames switched on this port

cat2600TsPortHashOverflows.name: cat2600TsPortHashOverflows
cat2600TsPortHashOverflows.description: Number of times a hash bucket was full when trying to add an entry to the port address table.

cat2600TsPortSwitchMode.name: cat2600TsPortSwitchMode
cat2600TsPortSwitchMode.description: Operational frame switching mode for the port. When in auto mode the port uses the Direct Cut algorithm to place the port in either cut-thru or store-and- forward mode. This object is equivalent to cPortProtocolCharFrameControlOption in the dtrMac MIB. However, this object defines an additional state -auto- not defined in that standard.

cat2600TsPortFixedCfg.name: cat2600TsPortFixedCfg
cat2600TsPortFixedCfg.description: Use fixed configuration or run auto detection to determine configuration.

cat2600TsPortMode.name: cat2600TsPortMode
cat2600TsPortMode.description: When read, this object indicates the Port Mode obtained by the auto-detect function. It is a valid read object only when TsPortFixedCfg is set to auto-detect(1) and TsPortLinkState indicates up(1). Write to this object when defining the Port Mode for a fixed configuration (TsPortFixedCfg set to fixed(2)). This object is equivalent to the dtrMac MIB object cPortProtocolCharOperationOption.

cat2600TsPortDuplex.name: cat2600TsPortDuplex
cat2600TsPortDuplex.description: Version 1 MIB When read, this object indicates the Port Duplex state obtained by the auto-detect function. This object is a valid read object any time that TSPortLinkState indicates up(1) or when TsPortFixedCfg indicates fixed(2). Write to this object when defining the Port Duplex state for a fixed configuration (TsPortFixedCfg set to fixed(2)). Version 2 MIB This object is related to the dtrMac MIB objects cPortProtocolCharCurrentAccessProtocol and cPortProtocolCharAccessProtcolMask as defined in the following table: TsPortLinkState | TsPortFixedCfg | TsPortDuplex equivalent to: | | down | auto | CPortProtocolCharAccess | | ProtocolMask = X'0003' | | down | fixed | CPortProtocolCharAccess | | ProtocolMask = X'0001' or | | = X'0002' | | up | auto | cPortProtocolCharCurrent | | AccessProtocol | | up | fixed | cPortProtocolCharCurrent | | AccessProtocol.

cat2600TsPortCfgLoss.name: cat2600TsPortCfgLoss
cat2600TsPortCfgLoss.description: Number of events as described in TsPortCfgLossRC after the port has completed the join process and then lost communication.

cat2600TsPortCfgLossRC.name: cat2600TsPortCfgLossRC
cat2600TsPortCfgLossRC.description: Reason code describing the cause of configuration loss.

cat2600TsPortCRCCount.name: cat2600TsPortCRCCount
cat2600TsPortCRCCount.description: Number of frames received with CRC error. This object is equivalent to dot5StatsLineError and to the dtrMac MIB object txiStatsLineErrorCounter.

cat2600TsPortHPChannelFrames.name: cat2600TsPortHPChannelFrames
cat2600TsPortHPChannelFrames.description: Number of frames sent to the high priority channel of the particular Token-Ring port.

cat2600TsPortLPChannelFrames.name: cat2600TsPortLPChannelFrames
cat2600TsPortLPChannelFrames.description: Number of frames sent to the low priority channel of the particular Token-Ring port.

cat2600TsPortHPThreshold.name: cat2600TsPortHPThreshold
cat2600TsPortHPThreshold.description: Priority level at which frames are sent to the High priority channel.

cat2600TsPortCfgRingSpeed.name: cat2600TsPortCfgRingSpeed
cat2600TsPortCfgRingSpeed.description: When read this object indicates the Port Ring Speed obtained by the RSA function. Write to this object when defining the Port Ring Speed for a fixed configuration (TsPortCfgRSA set to fixed(2)). When TsPortCfgRSA indicates fixed(2), this object is equivalent to the dtrMac MIB object cPortProtocolCharMediumRateOption and to dot5RingSpeed. Note that the syntax of these objects is different. For cPortProtocolCharMediumRateOption 1 indicates 4 Mb/s, while for TsPortCfgRingSpeed 1 indicates 16Mb/s. This object is a valid read object any time that TSPortLinkState indicates up(1)or when TsPortCfgRSA indicates fixed(2).

cat2600TsPortCfgRSA.name: cat2600TsPortCfgRSA
cat2600TsPortCfgRSA.description: User configured Ring Speed Adjust or fixed speed.

cat2600TsPortDomain.name: cat2600TsPortDomain
cat2600TsPortDomain.description: Domain that the port belongs to.

cat2600TsPortCfgLossThreshold.name: cat2600TsPortCfgLossThreshold
cat2600TsPortCfgLossThreshold.description: Number of configuration loss events (described in TsPortCfgLossRC) during the sample period which, if exceeded, should cause the port to be disabled. If the port is disabled by this function the port must be manually re-enabled.

cat2600TsPortCfgLossSamplingPeriod.name: cat2600TsPortCfgLossSamplingPeriod
cat2600TsPortCfgLossSamplingPeriod.description: The sampling period, in minutes, for which the port monitors to see if the configuration loss threshold has been exceeeded.

cat2600TsPortBeaconStationAddress.name: cat2600TsPortBeaconStationAddress
cat2600TsPortBeaconStationAddress.description: MAC address of the Station last generating a beacon MAC frame. This information is present for the generation of a trap and should not be used to represent the health of the ring.

cat2600TsPortBeaconNAUN.name: cat2600TsPortBeaconNAUN
cat2600TsPortBeaconNAUN.description: MAC address of the NAUN station last generating a beacon MAC frame. This information is present for the generation of a trap and should not be used to represent the health of the ring.

cat2600TsPortBeaconType.name: cat2600TsPortBeaconType
cat2600TsPortBeaconType.description: The type of Beacon which last occurred. Values are the same as for the Beacon Type subvector and are defined as follows: X'0001' Issued by a Dual Ring Station during reconfiguration X'0002' Signal Loss X'0003' Timer TCT expired during claim token; no claim token frames recieved X'0004' Timer TCT expired during claim token; claim token frames recieved X'0005' TXI Access Protocol; Heart Beat Protocol Failure

cat2600TsPortStnEntry.name: cat2600TsPortStnEntry
cat2600TsPortStnEntry.description: Definition of rows in the port table. The number of rows is determined by the hardware and is specified by the value of cat2600TsNumPorts. Rows can not be created or deleted via SNMP requests.

cat2600TsPortStnPortNum.name: cat2600TsPortStnPortNum
cat2600TsPortStnPortNum.description: Port number corresponding to this entry.

cat2600TsPortStnAddress.name: cat2600TsPortStnAddress
cat2600TsPortStnAddress.description: Station MAC address. Equivalent to ifPhysAddr for this port.

cat2600TsPortStnSrcFrames.name: cat2600TsPortStnSrcFrames
cat2600TsPortStnSrcFrames.description: Number of frames with this station as the source.

cat2600TsPortStnSrcBytes.name: cat2600TsPortStnSrcBytes
cat2600TsPortStnSrcBytes.description: Number of Bytes with this station as the source.

cat2600TsPortStnDestnFrames.name: cat2600TsPortStnDestnFrames
cat2600TsPortStnDestnFrames.description: Number of frames with this station as the destination.

cat2600TsPortStnDestnBytes.name: cat2600TsPortStnDestnBytes
cat2600TsPortStnDestnBytes.description: Number of bytes with this station as the destination.

cat2600TsOptPortStaTable.name: cat2600TsOptPortStaTable
cat2600TsOptPortStaTable.description: A table of station addresses known at an individual port. This table is designed to reduce the number of SNMP GETNEXT requests. This is done by packing many values into an octet string. (The maximum size frame should be used to return the result.) The instance returned for a GETNEXT is the value that identifies the last 'row' in the octet string. When the table is completely retrieved with one or more GETNEXTs, duplicate entries may be present, and entries may be skipped if the table is changing while being retrieved.

cat2600TsOptPortStaEntry.name: cat2600TsOptPortStaEntry
cat2600TsOptPortStaEntry.description: Definition of the rows in the optimized port station address table. Rows can not be created or deleted via SNMP requests.

cat2600TsOptPortStaPos.name: cat2600TsOptPortStaPos
cat2600TsOptPortStaPos.description: Second index for items in the optimized port station address table.

cat2600TsOptPortStaVal.name: cat2600TsOptPortStaVal
cat2600TsOptPortStaVal.description: An OCTET STRING containing a multiple number of stations from a port station address table. Each entry is encoded in the following format: Station MAC address - 6 octets Location 1 - local 2 - remote - 1 octet Port of exit Mask - 4 octets Source Frame Count - 4 octets (integer in little endian) Destn Frame Count - 4 octets (integer in little endian) Source Byte Count - 4 octets (integer in little endian) Destn Byte Count - 4 octets (integer in little endian) The Port of exit mask is encoded in its raw form as stored in the switch. Octet 1 Bit position 7 6 5 4 3 2 1 0 Port Number 31 30 29 28 27 26 25 24 Octet 2 Bit position 7 6 5 4 3 2 1 0 Port Number 23 22 21 20 19 18 17 16 Octet 3 Bit position 7 6 5 4 3 2 1 0 Port Number 15 14 13 12 11 10 9 8 Octet 4 Bit position 7 6 5 4 3 2 1 0 Port Number 7 6 5 4 3 2 1 CPU

cat2600TsDmnTable.name: cat2600TsDmnTable
cat2600TsDmnTable.description: Currently active domains on the switch.

cat2600TsDmnEntry.name: cat2600TsDmnEntry
cat2600TsDmnEntry.description: Definition of each row in the domain Table

cat2600TsDmnPorts.name: cat2600TsDmnPorts
cat2600TsDmnPorts.description: The set of ports that belong to this Domain. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the TokenRing Switch is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'. Warning: You will not receive a set- complete message as a set to this object causes the ports to reset.

cat2600TsDmnIpState.name: cat2600TsDmnIpState
cat2600TsDmnIpState.description: IP configuration method for this domain.

cat2600TsDmnIpAddress.name: cat2600TsDmnIpAddress
cat2600TsDmnIpAddress.description: The IP Address of this Domain. Changes to this object will take effect immediately.

cat2600TsDmnIpSubnetMask.name: cat2600TsDmnIpSubnetMask
cat2600TsDmnIpSubnetMask.description: The subnet mask for this domain. Changes to this object will take effect immediately.

cat2600TsDmnIpDefaultGateway.name: cat2600TsDmnIpDefaultGateway
cat2600TsDmnIpDefaultGateway.description: The IP Address of the default gateway for this Domain. Changes to this object will take effect immediately.

cat2600TsDmnStp.name: cat2600TsDmnStp
cat2600TsDmnStp.description: Turn Spanning tree on or off. Changes to this object will take effect immediately. The Spanning Tree Objects themselves are in the dtrConc MIB.

cat2600TsDmnName.name: cat2600TsDmnName
cat2600TsDmnName.description: User assigned name for each domain.

cat2600TsDmnIfIndex.name: cat2600TsDmnIfIndex
cat2600TsDmnIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the interface entry corresponding to each configured domain.

cat2600TsDmnBaseBridgeAddr.name: cat2600TsDmnBaseBridgeAddr
cat2600TsDmnBaseBridgeAddr.description: Base MAC address of this domain. Internally equivalent to dtrCRFMacAddress and to ifPhysAddress of the 'Domain' port.

cat2600TsDmnNumStations.name: cat2600TsDmnNumStations
cat2600TsDmnNumStations.description: Aggregate number of currently active stations (nodes) on all ports in the domain.

cat2600TsDmnMostStations.name: cat2600TsDmnMostStations
cat2600TsDmnMostStations.description: Highest aggregate number of stations ever active on all ports at one time, since the last reset or power cycle.

cat2600TsDmnStationEntry.name: cat2600TsDmnStationEntry
cat2600TsDmnStationEntry.description: Definition of each row in the domain specific station table. The object is equivalent to dtrFdbDynamicAddrTable or dtrFdbStaticAddrTable depending if the entry is learned or is a configured filter.

cat2600TsDmnStationDmnIndex.name: cat2600TsDmnStationDmnIndex
cat2600TsDmnStationDmnIndex.description: Integer reference to the domain number in the domain table.

cat2600TsDmnStationPort.name: cat2600TsDmnStationPort
cat2600TsDmnStationPort.description: The source port for the Station. The dtrConc MIB equivalents are dtrFdbDynamicAddrPortNumber and dtrFdbStaticAddrPortNumber.

cat2600TsDmnStationTraffic.name: cat2600TsDmnStationTraffic
cat2600TsDmnStationTraffic.description: A bit string that identifies the ports that this station has generated traffic to or from. The bits correspond to ports, with bits and ports numbered from right to left so that bit 0 represents the CPU, bit 1 represents port 1, and so forth. For example, the returned string 01 4D can be expanded to: 00000001 01001101 binary representation of object string xxxxxxx8 7654321C ports corresponding to bits This indicates ports 8, 6, 3, 2 and the CPU. The size of this string is adjusted to include all ports with traffic.

cat2600TsOptDmnStaTable.name: cat2600TsOptDmnStaTable
cat2600TsOptDmnStaTable.description: A table of station addresses known at an individual port. This table is designed to reduce the number of SNMP GETNEXT requests. This is done by packing many values into an octet string. (The maximum size frame should be used to return the result.) The instance returned for a GETNEXT is the value that identifies the last 'row' in the octet string. When the table is completely retrieved with one or more GETNEXTs, duplicate entries may be present, and entries may be skipped if the table is changing while being retrieved.

cat2600TsOptDmnStaEntry.name: cat2600TsOptDmnStaEntry
cat2600TsOptDmnStaEntry.description: Definition of the rows in the optimized domain station address table. Rows can not be created or deleted via SNMP requests.

cat2600TsOptDmnStaPos.name: cat2600TsOptDmnStaPos
cat2600TsOptDmnStaPos.description: Second index for items in the optimized port station address table.

cat2600TsOptDmnStaVal.name: cat2600TsOptDmnStaVal
cat2600TsOptDmnStaVal.description: An OCTET STRING containing a multiple number of stations from the domain station address table. Each entry is encoded in the following format: Station MAC address - 6 octets Port of Entry - 1 octet Traffic Mask - 4 octets The traffic mask is encoded in its raw form as stored in the switch. Octet 1 Bit position 7 6 5 4 3 2 1 0 Port Number 31 30 29 28 27 26 25 24 Octet 2 Bit position 7 6 5 4 3 2 1 0 Port Number 23 22 21 20 19 18 17 16 Octet 3 Bit position 7 6 5 4 3 2 1 0 Port Number 15 14 13 12 11 10 9 8 Octet 4 Bit position 7 6 5 4 3 2 1 0 Port Number 7 6 5 4 3 2 1 CPU

cat2600TsPipeEntry.name: cat2600TsPipeEntry
cat2600TsPipeEntry.description: Definition of each row in the TokenPipe table.

cat2600TsPipeNumber.name: cat2600TsPipeNumber
cat2600TsPipeNumber.description: The TokenPipe number for this row.

cat2600TsPipePorts.name: cat2600TsPipePorts
cat2600TsPipePorts.description: The set of ports in this switch which are active in this Pipe. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16 (if available), etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the NWays LAN Switch is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

cat2600TsFilterTable.name: cat2600TsFilterTable
cat2600TsFilterTable.description: Filters set up in the switch.

cat2600TsFilterEntry.name: cat2600TsFilterEntry
cat2600TsFilterEntry.description: Definition of each row in the filter table.

cat2600TsFilterStationAddress.name: cat2600TsFilterStationAddress
cat2600TsFilterStationAddress.description: The MAC address in a frame to which this entry's filtering information applies.

cat2600TsFilterType.name: cat2600TsFilterType
cat2600TsFilterType.description: There are two types of filters (i) source filters which act on the source address portion of a packet and (ii) destination filters which act on the destination address portion of a packet.

cat2600TsFilterStatus.name: cat2600TsFilterStatus
cat2600TsFilterStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. valid(1) - this entry is currently in use and will remain so after the next reset of the bridge. invalid(2) - writing this value to the object removes the corresponding entry.

cat2600TsFilterPorts.name: cat2600TsFilterPorts
cat2600TsFilterPorts.description: The set of ports to which this filter is applied. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the TokenRing Switch is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'. All frames with destination address equal to the station address corresponding to this entry and entering from any of the specified ports will be dropped. Setting this object with a MIB instance corresponding to the dotted decimal MAC address and a filter type, with the set value equal to the mask of ports you want to filter will create an entry in the table. Ex. MIB instance: 16.0.90.3.0.36.1 SNMP set value: 7F 00 00 00 This would create a filter entry with the following characteristics: MAC Address: 10 00 5A 03 00 24 (canonical format) Filter Type: source-filter Filter Ports: 2 3 4 5 6 7 8

cat2600TsFilterMask.name: cat2600TsFilterMask
cat2600TsFilterMask.description: The filter mask for this station. The semantics of the filter mask depend on the type of filter. For a source filter, the mask gives the ports that are allowed to receive frames from the filtered address. For a destination filter, the mask gives the ports that are forced to receive frames destined to the filtered address. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16 (if available), etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the switch is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

cat2600TsUFCNumPhysIfs.description: The total number of physical network interfaces on the UFC. This count does not include the interface _OF_ the card or any logical interfaces which be _ON_ the card.

cat2600TsUFCReset.name: cat2600TsUFCReset
cat2600TsUFCReset.description: The object is used to reset a UFC. Writing a softReset(3) causes the switch to reset the hardware, run the minimum number of diagnostics, and clear all counters. Writing hardReset(2) causes the UFC to run power up diagnostics and then execute a softreset.
